Cape Town police are investigating cases of murder and attempted murder after a worshipper was gunned down and another wounded during a shooting at a mosque in Khayelitsha on the Cape Flats earlier this week. Police spokesperson, Noloyiso Rwexana, says a 30-year-old man died on the scene during the incident in Harare. “According to information, a 30-year-old man was shot and fatally wounded while the other was transported to a medical facility for treatment. No one has been arrested at this stage,” says Rwexana. 